programme.title: The Young and the Restless
programme.desc: An iconic, enduring soap opera, this is the steamer set in Genoa City, where the Newman and Abbott dynasties stir it up in the bedroom and the boardroom. Best known for long-term love triangles, issue-oriented plots, a multi-ethnic cast and slick production values, 'Y&R' has been showered with Emmys, launched countless careers and spawned the equally lavish 'The Bold and the Beautiful.' Former cast members include Tom Selleck and David Hasselhoff. (New).

programme.title: The Bold and the Beautiful
programme.desc: The high-glam soap about L.A.'s fashionable and fertile Forrester clan was designed as a sister soap to the popular 'The Young and the Restless,' and quickly won ratings and global fans with cast crossovers, exotic remotes, glossy runway shows and fast-paced storylines about beautiful people behaving badly. In 2004, the show introduced a new family, the Marones, and recruited several nighttime alums to beef up the cast. And to create a little chaos. (New).

programme.title: American Experience
programme.desc: Recalling the tidal wave of racial conflict that followed in the wake of the surging Mississippi as it inundated the delta town of Greenville, Miss., in April 1927. Greenville's leading planter, LeRoy Percy, was a racial moderate, but he joined other planters in refusing to allow their black workers to be evacuated for fear of losing their labor supply. Those workers were placed "at the end of the line" for Red Cross supplies, as one remembers, and tension grew. Liev Schreiber narrates. (Repeat).

programme.title: American Experience

programme.title: The Silencers
programme.desc: A boozing, womanizing spy is coaxed out of retirement by an ex-girlfriend. His mission is to stop the evil Big O organization, whose leader plots to sabotage an atomic missile and thus spark World War III. (Repeat).

programme.title: Murderers' Row
programme.desc: A sleuth (Dean Martin) copes with beautiful girls and an archvillain (Karl Malden). Suzie: Ann-Margret. Dr. Solaris: Richard Eastham. Coco: Camilla Sparv. Ironhead: Tom Reese. MacDonald: James Gregory. Henry Levin directed. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Bounty Killer
programme.desc: Easterner (Dan Duryea) kills an outlaw, becomes a professional gun-for-hire, and hastens to ruin. Richard Arlen, Buster Crabbe, Fuzzy Knight, Johnny Mack Brown, Bob Steele, Audrey Dalton. Good story, belabored in the telling. Directed by Spencer Gordon Bennet. (Repeat).

programme.title: Big Bad Mama
programme.desc: Farcical melodrama with Angie Dickinson as a bank robber of the 1930s. Baxter: William Shatner. Fred: Tom Skerritt. Billy Jean: Susan Sennett. Polly: Robbie Lee. Barney: Noble Willingham. Directed by Steve Carver. (Repeat).

programme.title: Crazy Mama
programme.desc: Melodrama covering 30 years in the criminal lives of an Arkansas family. Cloris Leachman, Stuart Whitman. Sheba: Ann Sothern. Albertson: Jim Backus. Shawn: Donny Most. Cheryl: Linda Purl. Snake: Bryan Englund. Sheba (1932): Tisha Sterling. Bertha: Merie Earle. Ella Mae: Sally Kirkland. Daniel: Clint Kimbrough. Homer: Vince Barnett. Directed by Jonathan Demme. (Repeat).

programme.title: North to Alaska
programme.desc: Prospecting partners in Alaska find gold, prompting one to ask the other if he will escort the man's fiance on a journey to join them. (Repeat).

programme.title: Escape From Fort Bravo
programme.desc: In the Arizona territory, a ruthless Union Army captain undertakes a mission to recapture escaped Confederate prisoners and runs into an Apache hunting party. (Repeat).

programme.title: Little Women
programme.desc: Adaptation of Louisa May Alcott's classic slice of Americana about the four spirited March sisters and details their adventures, ambitions and romances in 1860s Massachusetts. (Repeat).

programme.title: Cactus Flower
programme.desc: A middle-aged dentist has taken on a much younger girlfriend. At first feigning fear of commitment because of his wife and children, and then falling for his young lover, the dentist implores the help of his nurse to pose as the wife he claims to have. (Repeat).

programme.title: Hopscotch
programme.desc: A CIA operative retires when his boss finds out that he let a KGB assassin escape. The operative begins writing a tell-all memoir, which causes him to go on the run from his former employers when they find out. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Men Who Stare at Goats
programme.desc: This uproarious comedy stars Ewan McGregor as a reporter who helps a U.S. soldier find the officer responsible for creating a top-secret program that trains warriors to develop psychic powers. The two learn that the officer is engaged in a personal feud with a spiritualist, and the program itself may soon disappear. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Ambushers
programme.desc: Superagent Matt Helm trails another power-mad spy chief, this time in Mexico. His mission is to secure a flying-saucer weapon that's fatal to men, but not to women. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Wrecking Crew
programme.desc: Fourth and final in the Matt Helm series with Dean Martin as the special agent, this time up against some lethal lovelies and a super-villain bent on stealing a billion dollars in gold bullion, which could possibly affect a collapse of the world economy. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Bravados
programme.desc: A rancher arrives in a small western town to witness the hanging of the men whom he holds responsible for the murder of his wife. Through the help of a duplicitous executioner, the gang escape and the vengeful rancher sets out to hunt the fugitives down. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Lady Vanishes
programme.desc: Vintage Hitchcock about an elderly English governess who disappears from a train, a fact that doesn't particularly concern other passengers except for a young lady she'd befriended and who's become convinced that somthing is amiss.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Game
programme.desc: A psychotic hunter arranges a shipwreck that will allow him to track and kill human prey. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Window
programme.desc: A young boy who is prone to lying claims to have witnessed a killing take place in a neighboring New York City apartment, but can't get anyone to believe him---except the murderers. The film is from a story by Cornell Woolrich, who wrote a similarly themed tale that was adapted for Hitchcock's "Rear Window." (Repeat).

programme.title: Panic in the Streets
programme.desc: Police try to nab killers who may carry the bubonic plague. (Repeat).

programme.title: Mildred Pierce
programme.desc: Joan Crawford won an Academy Award as a spurned housewife struggling to care for her two daughters: a lovable tomboy and a scheming, social-climbing teen who almost drives her to ruin. The film, an adaptation of James M. Cain's novel, was nominated for Best Picture. (Repeat).

programme.title: Framed
programme.desc: A young engineer meets and falls prey to a seductress. Before long he is unwittingly involved in an embezzlement and murder plot. (Repeat).

programme.title: The House on 92nd Street
programme.desc: Nazi spies in America recruit a German-American college student, who promptly goes to the FBI. The Feds convince him to be come a double agent, and help them find the leader of this clan of saboteurs. (Repeat).

programme.title: They Won't Believe Me
programme.desc: A cheating husband is put on trial for murder and his story is told through flashbacks, illustrating that although he is guilty of many things, he is no killer. (Repeat).

programme.title: Out of the Past
programme.desc: A private eye tries to escape a sordid past by becoming the proprietor of a gas station in a mountain village, but his previous unscrupulous dealings return to haunt him when a former client he betrayed hires him to do another job. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Unsuspected
programme.desc: A popular radio-show host recites spooky murder mysteries on his program, and the homicides he presents contain intimate and excruciating details because he had committed the actual crimes in real life. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Inside the Walls of Folsom Prison
programme.desc: A guard (David Brian) is for prison reform; the warden (Ted de Corsia) is against it. Daniels: Steve Cochran. Red: Philip Carey. Frazier: Scott Forbes. Ferretti: William Campbell. Daly: Lawrence Tolan. Filmed at Folsom. Directed by Crane Wilbur. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Crime Wave
programme.desc: Familiar cops-and-robbers yarn. Sims: Sterling Hayden. Steve: Gene Nelson. Ellen: Phyllis Kirk. Doc: Ted de Corsia. Hastings: Charles Buchinsky (Bronson). Johnny: Timothy Carey. Directed by Andre de Toth. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Call Northside 777
programme.desc: A reporter starts to believe the convicted killer he is writing human-interest stories about is innocent. The deeper the reporter digs into the original investigation, the more he begins to suspect that the police may be trying to keep something quiet. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Brewster's Millions
programme.desc: Penniless ex-GI Monty Brewster inherits $8 million from a rich relative, but there's a catch. To get the dough, he first has to spend a million in the course of a month, and nobody can know why he's doing it. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Dangerous Passage
programme.desc: Attempted sabotage on a boat. Joe: Robert Lowery. Nita: Phyllis Brooks. Bergstrom: Charles Arnt. Directed by William Berke. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Guns of Fort Petticoat
programme.desc: A Cavalryman goes AWOL after refusing to take part in the massacre of Cheyenne Indians. He trains a motley crew of women to defend themselves in the event of retaliation by American Indians. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Wackiest Ship in the Army
programme.desc: Tale of a secret mission to send an Australian spy to a remote Pacific island to keep track of the Japanese fleet during World War II. The decrepit ship and her inexperienced crew make for tough sailing for the lieutenant tasked with the assignment. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Bonnie and Clyde
programme.desc: The lives of Bonnie Parker and Clyde Barrow, notorious bank robbers of the early 1930s. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Bat 21
programme.desc: Story about efforts to rescue an Air Force colonel (Gene Hackman) shot down over Vietnam. Danny Glover. Col. Walker: Jerry Reed. Carver: David Marshall Grant. Sgt. Rumbaugh: Clayton Rohner. Maj. Scott: Erich Anderson. Directed by Peter Markle. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Acts of Violence
programme.desc: After human traffickers kidnap his fiancée, a man teams up with his ex-soldier brothers to rescue her in this intense action film. Their search leads them to a cop investigating trafficking rings, who soon joins their cause to bring down the organization for good. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: I See You
programme.desc: When a 12 year-old boy goes missing, investigator Greg Harper struggles to balance the pressure of the investigation and troubles with his wife, Jackie. Facing a recent affair, great strain is put on the family and slowly gnaws away at Jackie's grip on reality. But after a malicious presence manifests itself in their home and puts their son, Connor, in mortal danger, the cold, hard truth about evil in the Harper household is finally uncovered. (Repeat).(n)
